06/06/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Some 350-400 officers laid off from the Bulgarian Army will be hired by the customs sector, Defence Minister Nikolay Svinarov announced Sunday (5 June). 
The officers are expected to take over management positions at the customs administration, especially at border checkpoints. 
According to Svinarov, the move is aimed at strengthening the fight against corruption in the customs sector. 
He added that the border police would employ army reserve officers. 
(Standart, Monitor - 06/06/05)
